sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server
    participant database
    
    Note right of browser: User types a new note and clicks 'Save'
    
    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note
    activate server
    server-->>database: Insert new note into the database
    deactivate server
    
    Note right of server: Server processes the request, inserts the note into the database
    
    database-->>server: Confirmation of successful insertion
    activate server
    server-->>browser: Response: Note saved successfully
    deactivate server
    
    Note right of browser: Browser receives the response, displays a success message
    
    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
    activate server
    server-->>browser: Updated list of notes (including the new one)
    deactivate server
    
    Note right of browser: Browser fetches the updated list of notes from the server
    
    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the JavaScript file
    deactivate server
    
    Note right of browser: The browser starts executing the JavaScript code to update the UI
    
    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: Updated JSON data with the new note
    deactivate server
    
    Note right of browser: The browser executes the callback function to render the updated notes list

